body:
Thanks for taking the time to report this.

Can you please attach an example that shows the issue or missing feature?
```systemverilog
interface test_if #(
    parameter type test_type_t = logic
) ();
    test_type_t x;
endinterface

module t ();
    typedef logic [3:0] test_type_t;
    test_if #(.test_type_t(test_type_t)) test_if ();
    localparam TEST_TYPE_W = $bits(test_if.test_type_t);
    logic [TEST_TYPE_W-1:0] int_test;

    assign int_test = 4'd6;

    assign test_if.x = int_test;
endmodule
```

What output from that test indicates it is wrong, and what is the correct or expected output?  (Or, please make test self-checking if possible.)
This test doesn't compile with the following error:
```
%Error: t/t_interface_param_type_bits.v:10:44: Found definition of 'test_if.test_type_t' as a PARAMTYPEDTYPE but expected a variable/method
   10 |     localparam TEST_TYPE_W = $bits(test_if.test_type_t);
      |                                            ^~~~~~~~~~~
        ... See the manual at https://verilator.org/verilator_doc.html?v=5.040 for more assistance.
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

What 'verilator' command line do we use to run your example?
`$ verilator --cc --exe --build -j 0 -Wall top.sv`

What 'verilator --version' are you using?  Did you try it with the git master version?  Did you try it with other simulators?
`Verilator 5.040 2025-08-30 v5.040-50-g0a9d9db5a`

Yes, I tried this with master as well, results in the same compile error. This snippet compiles and works with ModelSim/Questa.

What OS and distribution are you using?
Fedora 29

